  "local_port": 59596,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "My driving license is lost. How do I apply for a new one?",
  "response": "To apply for a replacement driving license if yours is lost, follow these steps:\n\n1. **Report the Loss:**\n   - Contact your local Department of Motor Vehicles (DMV) or equivalent licensing authority immediately to report the loss. This can often be done online, by phone, or in person.\n\n2. **Gather Necessary Documents:**\n   - You'll typically need to provide identification such as a passport, birth certificate, or Social Security number.\n   - Proof of address, like a utility bill or lease agreement, may also be required.\n\n3. **Complete the Application:**\n   - Fill out the application form for a replacement license. This can usually be done online or at a DMV office.\n   - Some regions allow you to apply by mail, but this varies by location.\n\n4. **Pay the Fee:**\n   - There is usually a fee for replacing a lost license. Check the specific amount with your local DMV.\n\n5. **Submit the Application:**\n   - If applying in person, bring your completed form and required documents to the DMV.\n   - If applying online or by mail, follow the instructions provided by your local DMV for submitting your application and documents.\n\n6. **Wait for Processing:**\n   - The time it takes to receive your new license can vary. It may be mailed to you or available for pickup, depending on local policies.\n\n7. **Temporary License:**\n   - In some cases, you might be issued a temporary license while waiting for your permanent one.\n\n**Additional Tips:**\n- If your license was stolen, consider filing a police report as well.\n- Keep an eye on your credit reports and consider a fraud alert if you believe your identity might be at risk.\n\nFor specific instructions, it's best to visit the official website of your local DMV or contact them directly, as procedures can vary by state or country.",
